{{infobox football tournament season | title = Uganda Cup | year = 1979 | other_title = | image = | imagesize = | caption = | country = {{UGA}} | num_teams = | defending champions = | champions = [[Kampala City Council FC]] | runner-up = Uganda Commercial Bank FC | matches = | goals = | top goal scorer = | player = | prevseason = [[1978 Uganda Cup|1978]] | nextseason = [[1980 Uganda Cup|1980]] }} {{1979 football in Uganda}} '''[[Ugandan Cup |Uganda Cup]] 1979''' was the fifth season of the main Ugandan [[Association football|football]] Cup.
==Overview== The competition has also been known as the '''Kakungulu Cup''' and was won by [[Kampala City Council FC]] who were awarded a walk-over for their match against Uganda Commercial Bank FC in the final. The results are not available for the earlier rounds<ref name="RSSSF">{{cite news |title= Uganda - List of Cup Finals - RSSSF (Mikael Jönsson, Ian King and Hans Schöggl) |publisher=RSSSF Archive |year=1997–2013 |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tableso/oegcuphist.html |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref><ref name="Kawowo Sports">{{cite web |url= http://www.kawowo.com/index.php/football/item/13292-uganda-cup-past-finalists.html|title= Uganda Cup Past Finalists |work=Kawowo Sports |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref><ref name="Soccer256">{{cite web |url= http://soccer256.com/Kakungulu%20Cup%20winners.htm|title= Tournaments: Kakungulu cup |work=Soccer256 Magazine |accessdate=2014-01-22}}</ref>
