===[[Major League Baseball]]=== *April 2 – October 1: [[2017 Major League Baseball season]] ** [[American League]] winners: {{flagicon|Texas}} [[2017 Houston Astros season|Houston Astros]] ** [[National League]] winners: {{flagicon|California}} [[2017 Los Angeles Dodgers season|Los Angeles Dodgers]] *June 12 – 14: [[2017 Major League Baseball draft]] in {{flagicon|New Jersey}} [[Secaucus, New Jersey]] ** [[List of first overall Major League Baseball draft picks|#1 pick]]: {{flagicon|California}} [[Royce Lewis]] (to the {{flagicon|Minnesota}} [[Minnesota Twins]] from {{flagicon|California}} [[JSerra Catholic High School]]) *July 11: [[2017 Major League Baseball All-Star Game]] in {{flagicon|Florida}} [[Miami]] at [[Marlins Park]] ** The [[American League]] defeated the [[National League]], 2–1. ** [[Major League Baseball All-Star Game Most Valuable Player Award|MVP]]: {{flagicon|DOM}} [[Robinson Canó]] ({{flagicon|Washington}} [[2017 Seattle Mariners season|Seattle Mariners]]) ** [[2017 Major League Baseball Home Run Derby]] winner: {{flagicon|California}} [[Aaron Judge]] ({{flagicon|New York}} [[2017 New York Yankees season|New York Yankees]]) ** 2017 [[All-Star Futures Game]]: The World Team defeated the {{USA}}, 7–6. ** 2017 All-Star Futures Game MVP: {{flagicon|Georgia (U.S. state)}} [[Brent Honeywell]] ({{flagicon|Florida}} [[2017 Tampa Bay Rays season|Tampa Bay Rays]]) *October 24 – November 1: [[2017 World Series]] ** The {{flagicon|Texas}} [[2017 Houston Astros season|Houston Astros]] defeated the {{flagicon|California}} [[2017 Los Angeles Dodgers season|Los Angeles Dodgers]], 4–3 in games played, to win their first World Series title.
===[[World Baseball Softball Confederation|WBSC]]=== * July 28 – August 6: [[2017 12U Baseball World Cup]] in {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Tainan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wbsc.org/tournaments/2017-u12-baseball-world-cup/|title=Tournaments – WBSC|website=www.wbsc.org}}</ref> ** The {{USA}} defeated {{TPE}}, 7–2, to win their third consecutive 12U Baseball World Cup title. {{MEX}} took third place. * September 1 – 10: [[2017 U-18 Baseball World Cup]] in {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Thunder Bay]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wbsc.org/tournaments/2017-u18-baseball-world-cup/|title=Tournaments – WBSC|website=www.wbsc.org}}</ref> ** The {{USA}} defeated {{KOR}}, 8–0, to win their fourth consecutive and ninth overall U-18 Baseball World Cup title. {{JPN}} took third place.
===[[Little League Baseball]] tournaments=== * July 29 – August 5: 2017 [[Senior League World Series]] in {{flagicon|South Carolina}} [[Easley, South Carolina|Easley]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slbws.org/|title=Senior League Baseball World Series|website=Senior League Baseball World Series}}</ref> ** {{flagicon|PAN}} [[Senior League World Series (Latin America Region)|Team Latin America]] ([[Aguadulce, Coclé]]) defeated {{flagicon|USA}} Team [[Senior League World Series (South Region)|Southeast]] ({{flagicon|Florida}} [[Coral Springs, Florida|Coral Springs]]), 5–4, in the final. * July 30 – August 6: 2017 [[Intermediate League World Series]] in {{flagicon|California}} [[Livermore, California|Livermore]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://intermediateworldseries.org/|title=2017 Little League Intermediate World Series – 2017 Little League Intermediate Division World Series|website=2017 Little League Intermediate Division World Series}}</ref> ** {{flagicon|PUR}} Team [[Intermediate League World Series (Latin America Region)#Region Champions|Puerto Rico]] defeated {{flagicon|USA}} Team [[Intermediate League World Series (East Region)|East]] ({{flag|New Jersey}}), 6–5, in the final. * August 13 – 20: 2017 [[Junior League World Series]] in {{flagicon|Michigan}} [[Taylor, Michigan|Taylor]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cityoftaylor.com/653/Junior-League-World-Series|title=Junior League World Series – Taylor, MI|website=www.cityoftaylor.com}}</ref> ** {{flagicon|TPE}} Team [[Junior League World Series (Asia–Pacific Region)|Asia–Pacific]] ([[Taoyuan, Taiwan]]) defeated {{flagicon|USA}} Team [[Junior League World Series (East Region)|East]] ({{flagicon|Pennsylvania}} [[Kennett Square, Pennsylvania|Kennett Square]]), 12–1, in the final. * August 17 – 27: [[2017 Little League World Series]] in {{flagicon|Pennsylvania}} [[South Williamsport, Pennsylvania|South Williamsport]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.llbws.org/gameinfo/schedule.htm|title=2017 Little League Baseball World Series Schedule and Results|website=www.llbws.org}}</ref> ** {{flagicon|JPN}} Team Japan ([[Kōtō|Tokyo Kitasuna]] LL) defeated {{flagicon|USA}} Team [[Little League World Series (Southwest Region)|Southwest]] ({{flagicon|Texas}} [[Lufkin, Texas|Lufkin]]), 12–2, in the final.
