A Asia Cup]] in {{flagicon|LIB}} [[Zouk Mosbeh]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.com/asiacup/2017|title=FIBA Asia Cup 2017|website=FIBA.basketball}}</ref> ** {{bk|AUS}} defeated {{bk|IRI}}, 79–56, to win their first FIBA Asia Cup title. ** {{bk|KOR}} took third place. * September 22 – 30: [[2017 FIBA Asia Champions Cup]] in {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Chenzhou]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/asiachampionscup/2017|title=FIBA Asia Champions Cup 2017|website=FIBA.basketball}}</ref> ** {{flagicon|LIB}} [[Sporting Al Riyadi Beirut|Al Riyadi]] defeated {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Xinjiang Flying Tigers|China Kashgar]], 88–59, to win their second FIBA Asia Champions Cup title. ** {{flagicon|KAZ}} [[BC Astana]] took third place. * October 22 – 28: [[2017 FIBA Under-16 Women's Asian Championship]] in {{flagicon|IND}} Bangalore<ref>[http://www.fiba.basketball/asia/u16women/2017 FIBA's 2017 Under-16 Women's Asian Championship Page]</ref> ** {{bkwu|16|AUS}} defeated {{bkwu|16|JPN}}, 61–60, to win their first FIBA Under-16 Women's Asian Championship title. ** {{bkwu|16|CHN}} took third place. * October 27 – 29: FIBA 3x3 Asia Cup 2017 in {{flagicon|MGL}} [[Ulaanbaatar]]<ref>[http://www.fiba.basketball/3x3asiacup/2017 FIBA's 3x3 Asia Cup 2017 Page]</ref> ** {{3x3|MGL}} defeated {{3x3|NZL}}, 19–14, in the final. {{3x3|AUS}} took third place.
