ana Maria Furtado]] (f) ** Blitz winners: {{flagicon|VIE}} Trần Tuấn Minh (m) / {{flagicon|IRI}} Mobina Alinasab (f) ** Rapid winenrs: {{flagicon|VIE}} Trần Tuấn Minh (m) / {{flagicon|IND}} Isha Sharma (f) * May 11 – 12: [[Asian Chess Championship]] (individual and blitz) in {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Chengdu]] ** Winners: {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Wang Hao (chess player)|Wang Hao]] (m) / {{flagicon|VIE}} Võ Thị Kim Phụng (f) ** Blitz winners: {{flagicon|IND}} [[R. Vaishali]] (m) / {{flagicon|CHN}} Wei Yi (f) * June 2 – 10: 1st Asian Championship for Disabled in {{flagicon|KGZ}} [[Bishkek]] * June 17 – 26: Eastern Asia Youth Chess Championship 2017 in {{flagicon|MGL}} [[Ulanbaatar]] ** {{MGL}} won the gold medal tally and the overall medal tally. * July 20 – 30: Asian Schools Chess Championship (individual, rapid and blitz) in {{flagicon|CHN}} [[Panjin]] ** Open & girls overall winners: {{CHN}} * August 1 – 7: Western Asia Youth Chess Championship 2017 in {{SRI}} * August 1 – 8: Asian Club Cup Championship 2017 in {{SRI}} ** Winners: {{flagicon|IRI}} Saipa Chess Club, 2nd: {{flagicon|BAN}} Saif Sporting Chess Club, 3rd place: {{flagicon|AUS}} Sydney Chess Club * October 9 – 15: [[Asian Senior Chess Championship]] in {{flagicon|NZL}} [[Auckland]]
