==[[Korfball]]== ===World Cups and Continental Championships=== * April 13 – 17: 2017 U19 Korfball World Cup in {{flagicon|NED}} [[Leeuwarden]] ** In the final, {{korf|NED}} defeated {{korf|TPE}}, 28–16. ** {{korf|BEL}} took third place. * June 23 – 25: 2017 U17 Korfball World Cup in {{flagicon|NED}} [[Schijndel]] ** In the final, {{korf|NED}} defeated {{korf|BEL}}, 22–11. ** {{korf|ENG}} took third place. * August 8 – 13: IKF Asia U19 & U16 Korfball4 Championship in {{HKG}} * August 19 & 20: IKF Open European Beach Korfball Championship 2017 in {{flagicon|NED}} [[The Hague]] ** U19: In the final, {{korf|NED}} 2 defeated {{korf|HUN}}, 8–6. ** {{korf|BEL}} 1 took third place. ** Seniors: In the final, {{korf|NED}} 2 defeated {{korf|POR}}, 8–4. ** {{korf|BEL}} 1 took third place.
===Europe=== * January 12 – 14: 2017 [[Korfball Europa Cup]] in {{NED}} ** In the final, {{flagicon|NED}} [[KV TOP]] defeated {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Boeckenberg KC]], 37–27, to win her 3rd Europa Cup. ** {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Trojans Korfball Club]] took third place. * January 27 – 29: 2017 [[Korfball Europa Shield]] in {{POR}} ** In the final, {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Bec Korfball Club]] defeated {{flagicon|GER}} Schweriner KC, 10–9, to win her 3rd consecutive Europa Shield. ** {{flagicon|POR}} CRC Quinta Dos Lombos took third place.
==[[Lacrosse]]== ===Lacrosse World Cup=== * July 12 – 22: [[2017 Women's Lacrosse World Cup]] in {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Guildford]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.englishlacrosse.co.uk/RWLC17/?dm_t=0,0,0,0,0|title=Home – FIL Rathbones Women's Lacrosse World Cup|website=FIL Rathbones Women's Lacrosse World Cup}}</ref> ** The {{USA}} defeated {{CAN}}, 10–5, to win their third consecutive and eighth overall Women's Lacrosse World Cup title. ** {{ENG}} won the bronze medal.
===[[Major League Lacrosse]]=== * April 22 – August 19: [[2017 Major League Lacrosse season]] ** The {{flagicon|Ohio}} [[2017 Ohio Machine season|Ohio Machine]] defeated the {{flagicon|Colorado}} [[2017 Denver Outlaws season|Denver Outlaws]], 17–12, to win their first Major League Lacrosse title.
===[[NCAA Lacrosse Championship]]=== * May 7 – 28: 2017 [[NCAA Division III Men's Lacrosse Championship]] at [[Gillette Stadium]] in {{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Foxborough, Massachusetts]] ** The {{flagicon|Maryland}} [[Salisbury University|Salisbury]] Sea Gulls defeated the {{flagicon|New York}} [[RIT Tigers]], 15–7, to win their second consecutive and 12th overall NCAA Division III Men's Lacrosse Championship title. * May 12 – 28: 2017 [[NCAA Division I Women's Lacrosse Championship]] at [[Gillette Stadium]] in {{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Foxborough, Massachusetts]] ** The {{flagicon|Maryland}} [[Maryland Terrapins women's lacrosse|Maryland Terrapins]] defeated the {{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Boston College Eagles]], 16–13, to win their 13th NCAA Division I Women's Lacrosse Championship title. * May 13 – 28: 2017 [[NCAA Division II Men's Lacrosse Championship]] at [[Gillette Stadium]] in {{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Foxborough, Massachusetts]] ** The {{flagicon|South Carolina}} [[Limestone Saints]] defeated the {{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Merrimack Warriors]], 11–9, to win their fifth NCAA Division II Men's Lacrosse Championship title. * May 13 – 29: [[2017 NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship]] at [[Gillette Stadium]] in {{flagicon|Massachusetts}} [[Foxborough, Massachusetts]] ** The {{flagicon|Maryland}} [[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland Terrapins]] defeated the {{flagicon|Ohio}} [[Ohio State Buckeyes men's lacrosse|Ohio State Buckeyes]], 9–6, to win their third NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship title. * May 19 – 21: 2017 [[NCAA Division II Women's Lacrosse Championship]] at BU Sports Stadium in {{flagicon|Pennsylvania}} [[Bloomsburg, Pennsylvania]] ** The {{flagicon|New York}} [[Adelphi Panthers]] defeated the {{flagicon|Florida}} [[Florida Southern Moccasins]], 6–4, to win their eighth NCAA Division II Women's Lacrosse Championship title. * May 27 & 28: 2017 [[NCAA Division III Women's Lacrosse Championship]] at Donald J. Kerr Stadium in {{flagicon|Virginia}} [[Salem, Virginia]] ** The {{flagicon|Pennsylvania}} [[Gettysburg College|Gettysburg Bullets]] defeated the {{flagicon|New Jersey}} [[The College of New Jersey|TCNJ Lions]], 6–5, to win their second NCAA Division III Women's Lacrosse Championship title.
