om/en/ World Games 2017 Website]</ref> ** {{RUS}} won both the gold and overall medal tallies. * July 21 – 30: [[2017 Jeux de la Francophonie]] in {{flagicon|CIV}} [[Abidjan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abidjan2017.ci/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150412190327/http://www.abidjan2017.ci/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2015-04-12|title=VIIIes Jeux de la Francophonie Abidjan 2017|website=www.abidjan2017.ci}}</ref> ** {{FRA}} won both the gold and overall medal tallies. * July 22 – 30: [[2017 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival]] in {{flagicon|HUN}} [[Győr]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gyor2017.hu/en_GB/home|title=European Youth Olympic Festival 2017|first=Teszt|last=Elek|date=25 July 2017|website=gyor2017.hu}}</ref> ** {{RUS}} won both the gold and overall medal tallies. * July 28 – August 13: [[2017 Canada Summer Games]] in {{flagicon|MB}} [[Winnipeg]]<ref>[http://www.2017canadagames.ca/ 2017 Canada Summer Games Website]</ref> ** {{ON}} won both the gold and overall medal tallies. * August 7 – 16: 2017 [[World Police and Fire Games]] in {{flagicon|USA}} [[Los Angeles]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.la17wpfg.com/6/scenes/Home.htm?win=Main|title=2017 World Police and Fire Games Los Angeles|website=www.la17wpfg.com}}</ref> ** Note: ''These Games was supposed to be in [[Montreal]], but it was relocated because of a boycott by the police and firefighter unions over pension reform.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/montreal-fire-police-games-cancelled-1.3499036|title=Montreal cancels 2017 World Police and Fire Games|publisher=}}</ref> ** For results, click [http://wpfg2017.fusesport.com/competitions.asp?id=215 here.] * August 19 – 30: [[2017 Summer Universiade]] in {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Taipei]]<ref>[http://www.taipei2017.com.tw/bin/home.php?Lang=en 2017 Summer Universiade Website]</ref> ** {{flagIOC2|JPN|2017 Summer Universiade|}} won both the gold and overall medal tallies. * August 19 – 31: [[2017 Southeast Asian Games]], in {{flagicon|