===World rugby league championships=== * October 26 – December 2: [[2017 Rugby League World Cup]] in {{AUS}}, {{NZL}} and {{PNG}} ** {{rl|AUS}} defeated {{rl|ENG}}, 6–0, to win their second consecutive and eleventh overall Rugby League World Cup title. * November 16 – December 2: [[2017 Women's Rugby League World Cup]] in {{AUS}} ** {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Australia women's national rugby league team|Australia]] defeated {{flagicon|NZL}} [[New Zealand women's national rugby league team|New Zealand]], 23–16, to win their second consecutive Women's Rugby League World Cup title.
===Club seasons and championships=== *February 18 & 19: [[2017 World Club Series]] in {{ENG}} **Game 1: {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Warrington Wolves]] defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Brisbane Broncos]], 27–18, at [[Halliwell Jones Stadium]], [[Warrington]] **Game 2 ([[World Club Challenge]]): {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Wigan Warriors]] defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks]], 22–6, at [[DW Stadium]], [[Wigan]] *February 9 – October 7: [[Super League XXII]] in {{ENG}} and {{FRA}} (final at {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Old Trafford]], [[Manchester]]) ** The {{leagueicon|Leeds|16}} [[Leeds Rhinos]] defeated the {{leagueicon|Castleford|16}} [[Castleford Tigers]], 24–6, to win their eighth Super League title. *March 2 – October 1: [[2017 NRL season]] in {{AUS}} and {{NZL}} ([[2017 NRL Grand Final|final]] at {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Stadium Australia]], [[Sydney]]) ** The {{leagueicon|Melbourne|16}} [[Melbourne Storm]] defeated the {{leagueicon|North Queensland|16}} [[North Queensland Cowboys]], 34–6, to win their third NRL title.
