{{Primary sources|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox college basketball team |current = 2017–18 Columbia Lions women's basketball team |name = Columbia Lions |logo = Columbia Lions wordmark.svg |logo_size = 250 |university = Columbia University |conference = [[Ivy League]] |firstseason = 1984 |record = 286–570 ({{Winning percentage|286|570}}) |location = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]] |coach = Megan Griffith |tenure = 1st |arena = [[Levien Gymnasium]] |studentsection = |capacity = 2,500 |nickname = [[Columbia Lions|Lions]] |h_body = 183863 |h_pattern_b =_Spikesonwhite |h_shorts = 183863 |h_pattern_s = _blanksides2 |a_body = 183863 |a_pattern_b=_Whitespikes |a_shorts = 183863 |a_pattern_s=_whitesides |NCAAchampion2 = |NCAAchampion = |NCAArunnerup = |NCAAfinalfour = |NCAAsweetsixteen = |NCAAtourneys = |conference_season = }} The '''Columbia Lions women's basketball team''' is the [[college basketball|intercollegiate women's basketball]] program representing [[Columbia University]]. The school competes in the [[Ivy League]] in [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] of the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] (NCAA). The [[Columbia Lions|Lions]] play home basketball games at the [[Levien Gymnasium]] in [[New York, New York]] on the university campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gocolumbialions.com/SportSelect.dbml?SPID=3887 |title=Women's Basketball – News – GoColumbiaLions.com—Official Web Site of Columbia University Athletics |website=Gocolumbialions.com |date= |accessdate=2017-01-26}}</ref>
==History== The Lions have a 286–570 record since beginning play in 1984 after Columbia went co-ed in 1983. They joined the [[Ivy League]] in women's basketball in 1986 after two seasons in Division III play. The women's teams used to be known as the Barnard Bears, named for the affiliated women's college of the same name. For their first 23 seasons, they never finished higher than fourth in the eight team conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gocolumbialions.com//pdf9/5085308.pdf?DB_OEM_ID=9600 |format=PDF |title=Columbia Basketball 2016–17 Record Book |website=Gocolumbialions.com |accessdate=2017-01-26}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" {{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Columbia Lions|Year|Record|Conference Record|Coach}} |- align="center" |- | style="text-align:left"| 1984–85 || 19–7 || n/a || Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1985–86 || 21–6 || n/a || Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1986–87 || 8–16 || 2–12 ||Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1987–88 || 12–14 || 4–10 || Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1988–89 || 12–14 || 5–9 || Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1989–90 || 12–14 || 5–9 || Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1990–91 || 10–16 || 5–9 || Nancy Kalafus |- | style="text-align:left"| 1991–92 || 4–22 || 1–13 || Kerry Phayre |- | style="text-align:left"| 1992–93 || 7–19 || 1–13 || Kerry Phayre |- | style="text-align:left"| 1993–94 || 4–22 || 2–12 || Kerry Phayre |- | style="text-align:left"| 1994–95 || 0–26 || 0–14 || Kerry Phayre |- | style="text-align:left"| 1995–96 || 2–24 || 1–13 || Kerry Phayre |- | style="text-align:left"| 1996–97 || 6–20 || 3–11 || Jay Butler |- | style="text-align:left"| 1997–98 || 4–22 || 0–14 || Jay Butler |- | style="text-align:left"| 1998–99 || 6–20 || 2–12 || Jay Butler |- | style="text-align:left"| 1999-00 || 7–19 || 6–8 || Jay Butler |- | style="text-align:left"| 2000–01 || 9–18 || 6–8 || Jay Butler |- | style="text-align:left"| 2002–03 || 11–16 || 4–10 || Jay Butler |- |