{{Infobox stadium | name = Stade of Oyem | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = Stade d'Oyem | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Oyem]], [[Gabon]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 2015 | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Government of Gabon]] | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = Shanghai General Construction | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = Shanghai General Construction | main_contractors = | capacity = 20,500 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = 105 x 68 m | acreage = | tenants = }}
The '''Stade d'Oyem''' is a stadium in [[Oyem]], [[Gabon]]. This 20,500<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thegabon.com/visit-of-oyem-stadium-site-by-the-head-of-state/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-10-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019143353/http://thegabon.com/visit-of-oyem-stadium-site-by-the-head-of-state/ |archivedate=2016-10-19 |df= }}</ref> capacity stadium opened for use in the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://thegabon.com/can-2017-oyem-stadium-60-completed/ | title=Can 2017: Oyem stadium 60% completed | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112134612/http://thegabon.com/can-2017-oyem-stadium-60-completed/ | archivedate=2017-01-12 | df= }}</ref> ==References==
